'''213''' ('''two hundred [and] thirteen''') is the number following [[212 (number)|212]] and preceding [[214 (number)|214]].
It is the smallest of a triple consecutive numbers that are products of two distinct [[prime number]]s: 213&nbsp;=&nbsp;3&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;71, 214&nbsp;=&nbsp;2&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;107, and 215&nbsp;=&nbsp;5&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;43.<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A039833|name=Smallest of three consecutive squarefree numbers n, n+1, n+2 of the form p*q where p and q are primes}}.</ref> Its square is a sum of distinct factorials: 213<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;=&nbsp;45369&nbsp;=&nbsp;1!&nbsp;+&nbsp;2!&nbsp;+&nbsp;3!&nbsp;+&nbsp;7!&nbsp;+&nbsp;8!.<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A014597|name=Numbers n such that n^2 is a sum of distinct factorials}}.</ref>
==See also== * [[213 (group)|213]], a hip hop music group * [[Area code 213]] * [[213 Lilaea]] a [[main belt]] asteroid. * [[+213]] is the code for international direct-dial phone calls to [[Algeria]].
